{"TopicId":161562,"ForumId":15,"TopicTitle":"How make normal maps for planets?","CreatedByName":"Danilka","CreatedById":176943,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T08:56:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Danilka","CreatedById":176943,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-04T08:56:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-05T13:58:44Z\u0022 title=\u002206/05/2017 01:58  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 5, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Danilka\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-06T21:39:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse this website\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://cpetry.github.io/NormalMap-Online/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://cpetry.github.io/NormalMap-Online/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Danilka","CreatedById":176943,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T05:31:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223082941\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022161562\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221496785168\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173044\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ModerndayLink64\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, ModerndayLink64 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse this website\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://cpetry.github.io/NormalMap-Online/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://cpetry.github.io/NormalMap-Online/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen using standard normal maps, an error occurs. To fix this error, you need to save normal maps with an alpha channel (in order to get a normal maps in RGBA format). And I don\u0027t know how to make this alpha channel.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022STZC6rz.png\u0022 height=\u0022511\u0022 src=\u0022http://i.imgur.com/STZC6rz.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-07T05:32:18Z\u0022 title=\u002206/07/2017 05:32  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 7, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Danilka\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ModerndayLink","CreatedById":173044,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-07T10:13:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, sorry then I have no clue how to do that either\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kurld","CreatedById":79950,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-07-03T12:52:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s going to be drawing-tool specific, but look for some menu or dialog that mentions \u0022channels\u0022 and typically there will be an option to add an alpha channel there.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KerikBalm","CreatedById":91917,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-03-26T11:42:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo its been some time since I made a planet, but I am trying to make a titan analogue (Tekto is nice, but not what I\u0027m looking for), and I\u0027m having the same problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI don\u0027t remember what I did last time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan anyone tell me what needs to be done to generate a proper normal map from a heightmap?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Iapetus7342","CreatedById":233205,"CreatedDateTime":"2024-06-08T18:20:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube-nocookie.com/embed/VL5B0nXi9cg?feature=oembed\u0022 title=\u0022How to Make a Kopernicus Planet | Kerbal Space Program\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis video covers Planet Creation well.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}